              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "xy"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " value 'polar'              you can specify "
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "theta"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": ", "
            },
            {
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "r"
                }
              ],
              "type": "emphasis"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": " for the annotation,                      even in cartesian plots.  Note that if you are                      using a polar axes, you do not need to specify                      polar for the coordinate system since that is the                      native \"data\" coordinate system. ==================== =================================================="
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Alternatively they can be set to any valid "
